  "prompt": "What is a good amount of money yearly to live more than comfortably in the USA?",
  "response": "The amount of money required to live more than comfortably in the USA can vary significantly depending on various factors such as location, lifestyle preferences, and family size. Generally speaking, in places with a lower cost of living, such as rural areas or smaller cities, you might find $60,000 to $80,000 per year sufficient for a comfortable lifestyle. However, in more expensive urban areas like New York City, San Francisco, or Los Angeles, you may need $150,000 to $200,000 or more annually to achieve a similar level of comfort.\n\nIt's important to consider the following aspects to determine what a comfortable lifestyle means to you:\n- Housing costs (rent or mortgage)\n- Utilities and other household expenses\n- Groceries and dining out\n- Transportation (owning a car, public transit, etc.)\n- Health care and insurance\n- Savings and investments\n- Entertainment and leisure activities\n- Education costs if you have children\n\nUltimately, what qualifies as \"more than comfortable\" will differ from person to person based on individual priorities and circumstances.",
